Thebe Magugu, Fashion Designer of the Year 2021. Source: Fashion Industry Awards SA via InstagramThe awards were developed to acknowledge and celebrate creative and business excellence that has positively impacted the local fashion landscape.Among the big winners of the Fashion Industry Awards South Africa 2021 were designer Jo Borkett, scooping the Lifetime Achievement Award; Thebe Magugu, winning Fashion Designer of the Year; Craig Jacobs, who walked off with Fashion Innovation of the Year; and The Space, which won Retail Space of the Year.Craig Jacobs named SA's first recipient of the Fashion Innovation AwardIssued by OnPoint PR 3 days agoView the full list of winners below.Lifetime Achievement Award: Jo BorkettFashion Designer of the Year:   Thebe MaguguEmerging Talent of the Year:   EzokhethoFashion Innovation of the Year:   Craig JacobsWomenswear Brand of the Year:   Palesa Mokubang for ManthsoMenswear Brand of the Year:   Naked Ape by Shaldon KopmanChildrenswear Designer of the Year:   Lullaby RockAccessory Designer of the Year:   PichulikTextile Designer of the Year:   Maxhosa AfricaHeritage/Cultural Designer of the Year:   Bongiwe WalazaAfrican Fashion Brand of the Year based in SA:   Anissa Mpungwe AtelierRetail Space of the Year:   The SpaceFashion Muse of the Year:   Yaya MavundlaCut, Make & Trim (CMT) of the Year:  Cloth CollectivePatternmaker of the Year:   Laughing Lizard Pattern CreationsSeamstress of the Year:   Bernadette DarisaneFashion Journalist of the Year:  Emmanuel TjiyaFashion Stylist of the Year:   Chloe Andrea WelgemoedView the awards ceremony here: